Both NativeNotify and Firebase offer real-time notification services, but which one to choose depends on your project requirements. Here's a comparison to help you decide:

1. Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM)
   ✅ Pros:

Free and scalable.
Well-integrated with Firebase Auth, Firestore, and Analytics.
Works across multiple platforms (Web, Android, iOS).
Supports both push and in-app messaging.
Advanced targeting and automation.
❌ Cons:

Requires setup with Firebase SDK.
Can be complex if you need advanced features like topic-based notifications. 2. NativeNotify
✅ Pros:

Easier to implement than Firebase.
Provides real-time notifications with simple integration.
Supports cross-platform notifications with minimal setup.
Built-in notification history and analytics.
❌ Cons:

Less flexible and customizable than Firebase.
May not scale as well for very large applications.
Which One Should You Choose?
If you want a simple and fast setup for notifications, NativeNotify is a good choice.
If you're already using Firebase for authentication or database, or need scalability and more control, Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM) is better.
📌 Recommendation for Your Project (TT Recrut System)
Since your project is already using MongoDB and MERN stack, Firebase might not be a natural fit unless you integrate it separately. If you want a quick and easy solution, go for NativeNotify. If you prefer full control and scalability, use Firebase FCM.

